solutions.content:
**Recursive**
* Base case: if `nums[index]` reached the end then `maxSoFar` will be the `nums[index]`
* recursive case: compare the current `nums[index]` with the sum of  current `nums[index]` from recursion output of the next `index+1`
* compute `maxOverall` and return at the end
```
class Solution {
	 private int maxOverall = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
     protected int recurse(int[] nums, int index){
         int maxSoFar = 0;
         if (index == nums.length-1)
             maxSoFar = nums[index];
         else
             maxSoFar = Math.max(nums[index], nums[index] + recurse(nums, index+1));
         maxOverall = Math.max(maxOverall, maxSoFar);
         return maxSoFar;
     }

     public int maxSubArray(int[] nums) {
         recurse(nums, 0);
         return maxOverall;
       }
}
```
**Bottom Up - DP**
* just converting the logic to `dp` array with recurrence of `maxSoFar = max(nums[i], nums[i] + dp[i-1])`
```
class Solution {
 public int maxSubArray(int[] nums) {
        int length = nums.length;
        int[] dp = new int[length];
        dp[0] = nums[0];
        int maxOverall = dp[0];
        for (int i=1;i<length;i++){
            dp[i] = Math.max(nums[i], dp[i-1] + nums[i]);
            maxOverall = Math.max(maxOverall, dp[i]);
        }
        return maxOverall;
    }
}
```
