solutions.content:
**INTUITION** :  here, this is pretty easy, we are getting a k sorted array,i.e.  partially sorted we can apply binary search.
 Now, to apply binary search, we need a binary criteria to divide our search space into 2 parts, which we can understand by looking at the graph below.
 ![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/f5b9ef72-66b8-4bcc-9d78-a2ce3e87220b_1643886247.7863996.png)
 1. Our goal is to reach the valley.
 2. If we are at any point between [ 4 ,7], we need to move right to reach the valley.
 3. If we are [1, 2], we need to go towards the left to reach the valley.
 Now, how do we figure out which part of the graph, our curr value lies in.
 4. If `curr value <nums[0]` , we lie in the [0,2] portion, else we move right.
 **Edge case:**
 In the second case, when we reach the peak, start becomes n, which means the array is not rotated, it is in a monotone unlike case 1.
**Code:**

 ```
class Solution {
public:
    int findMin(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n=nums.size();
        int start=0,end=n-1,mid=(start+end)/2;
        while(start<=end)
        {  

           if(nums[mid]>=nums[0])
               start=mid+1;         //go right
            else
              end=mid-1;          // go left.

            mid=(start+end)/2;
        }
        if(start==n)
            return nums[0];
        return nums[start];

    }
};
```

